addAdmin(address).details: Grants admin user privilages to newAdmin.

burn(uint256).details: Burns `tokenId`. See {ERC721-_burn}. Requirements: - The caller must own `tokenId` or be an approved operator.

burnLocked(uint256).details: See {ERC721-_burn}. This override additionally clears the royalty information for the token.

collectionURI(uint256).details: Gets URI for the token metadata

params.collectionId: ( uint256 ) The Event Id you want to get the URI

returns._0: ( string ) URI for the collection metadata

returns.forwarder: The address of the Forwarder contract that is being used.

isAdmin(address).details: Returns the true if the address is an admin user, else false.

params.tokenId: ( uint256 ) The token id to check.

returns._0: bool representing the token locked status

params.forwarder: The address of the Forwarder contract that is being used.

returns._0: isTrustedForwarder `true` if the Forwarder is trusted to forward relayed transactions by this Recipient.

lockToken(uint256).details: Locks a specific ERC721 token. Requires - The sender has to be the approved opperator - The contract does not have to be paused - The token cannot already be locked

params.tokenId: ( uint256 ) Id of the ERC721 token to be locked.

mintCollectionToManyUsers(uint256,addres.details: Mint token to many addresses. Requires - The msg sender to be the owner - The contract does not have to be paused

params.collectionId: ( uint256 ) CollectionId for the new token
params.expiration: ( unit64 ) timestamp when the token expires, 0 if not subscription token
params.locked: ( bool ) true if minted token should be locked, else false
params.to: ( array of address ) The addresses that will receive the minted tokens.

returns._0: lastId ( uint256 ) the tokenId of the last minted token.
returns._1: lastId ( uint256 ) the number of tokens minted.

mintToken(uint256,address,bool).details: Mint token to address. Requires - The msg sender to be the onwer - The contract does not have to be paused

params.collectionId: ( uint256 ) CollectionId for the new token
params.locked: ( bool ) true if minted token should be locked, else false
params.to: ( address ) The address that will receive the minted tokens.

returns._0: lastId ( uint256 ) the tokenId of the minted token.

mintTokenWithExpiration(uint256,address,.details: Mint token to address. Requires - The msg sender to be the onwer - The contract does not have to be paused

params.collectionId: ( uint256 ) CollectionId for the new token
params.expiration: ( unit64 ) timestamp when the token expires
params.locked: ( bool ) true if minted token should be locked, else false
params.to: ( address ) The address that will receive the minted tokens.

returns._0: lastId ( uint256 ) the tokenId of the minted token.

mintUserToManyCollections(uint256[],addr.details: Mint many tokens to address. Requires - The msg sender to be the admin - The contract does not have to be paused

params.collectionIds: ( array uint256 ) Collection Ids to assing to user
params.expiration: ( unit64 ) timestamp when the token expires, 0 if not subscription token
params.locked: ( bool ) true if minted token should be locked, else false
params.to: ( address ) The address that will receive the minted tokens.

returns._0: lastId ( uint256 ) the tokenId of the last minted token.
returns._1: lastId ( uint256 ) the number of tokens minted.

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

paused().details: Returns true if the contract is paused, and false otherwise.

proxiableUUID().details: Implementation of the ERC1822 {proxiableUUID} function. This returns the storage slot used by the implementation. It is used to validate the implementation's compatibility when performing an upgrade. IMPORTANT: A proxy pointing at a proxiable contract should not be considered proxiable itself, because this risks bricking a proxy that upgrades to it, by delegating to itself until out of gas. Thus it is critical that this function revert if invoked through a proxy. This is guaranteed by the `notDelegated` modifier.

removeAdmin(address).details: Revokes admin user privilages to admin.

removeCollectionRoyalty(uint256).details: Resets royalty information for the token id back to the global default.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

royaltyInfo(uint256,uint256).details: Returns how much royalty is owed and to whom, based on a sale price that may be denominated in any unit of exchange. The royalty amount is denominated and should be paid in that same unit of exchange.

setCollectionRoyalty(uint256,address,uin.details: Sets the royalty information for a specific collection, overriding the global default.

params.collectionId: the collection to set the royalty for
params.feeNumerator: Size of the royalty in basis points. Cannot be greater than the fee denominator (10000).
params.receiver: Address to receive the royalties. Cannot be the zero address.

setDefaultRoyalty(address,uint96).details: Sets the royalty information that all ids in this contract will default to.

params.feeNumerator: Size of the royalty in basis points. Cannot be greater than the fee denominator (10000).
params.receiver: Address to receive the royalties. Cannot be the zero address.

setExpiration(uint256,uint64).details: Sets the expiration time of the given token If the `tokenId` does not exist, an error will be thrown.

params.newExpiration: ( uint64 ) time that the token expires Emits a {SubscriptionUpdate} event after the subscription is modified.

setLastId(uint256).details: Sets Last Id for minting. Requires - The msg sender to be the admin - The contract does not have to be paused

setTrustedForwarder(address).details: Allows the owner to update the trusted forwarder for erc2771 transactions

params.forwarder: ( address ) contract address of the new forwarder

tokenCollection(uint256).details: Gets the Collection Id for the token

params.tokenId: ( uint256 ) The Token Id you want to query

returns._0: ( uint256 ) representing the Collection id for the token

tokenURI(uint256).details: Gets URI for the token metadata

params.tokenId: ( uint256 ) The Token Id you want to get the URI

returns._0: ( string ) URI for the token metadata

transferLockedToken(uint256,address,bool.details: Transfer a locked token from a token owner to the recipient's wallet Requires:  - msg sender to be the contract owner or admin

params.recipient: ( address ) address where the token will be sent
params.remainLocked: ( bool ) true if the token remains locked after transfer, else false
params.tokenId: ( uint256 ) Id of the token being reclaimed

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

unlockToken(uint256).details: Unlock a specific ERC721 token. Requires - The msg sender to be the owner - The contract does not have to be paused - The token must be locked

params.tokenId: ( uint256 ) Id of the ERC721 token to be unlocked.

updateName(string).details: Updates the name of the contrcat see: ERC721

params.newName: ( string ) The new name of the contract

params.newSymbol: ( string ) The new symbol of the contract

updateTokenCollection(uint256,uint256).details: updates the collection id of an already minted token

params.newCollectionId: ( uint256 ) the id of the token's new collection
params.tokenId: ( uint256 ) the id of the token that needs to be updated

upgradeTo(address).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

upgradeToAndCall(address,bytes).details: Upgrade the implementation of the proxy to `newImplementation`, and subsequently execute the function call encoded in `data`. Calls {_authorizeUpgrade}. Emits an {Upgraded} event.

getTrustedForwarder().notice: :warning: **Warning** :warning: The Forwarder can have a full control over your Recipient. Only trust verified Forwarder.Method is not a required method to allow Recipients to trust multiple Forwarders. Not recommended yet.
